## 🌐 Digital Portfolio Reflection

Building this digital portfolio represents a shift from being a passive consumer to an active creator.  
Over the next four years, I plan to use **GitHub** as the primary repository for my evolution in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning — moving from basic Python scripts to complex neural network projects.  

Simultaneously, **LinkedIn** will serve as my professional storefront, where I will document certifications, share project milestones, and connect with industry mentors to stay updated on AI trends.  

One challenge I faced during this task was **Authentic Branding** — presenting a "work-in-progress" student profile that still looks professional and credible to recruiters. To bridge this gap, I will use **HackerRank** to sharpen my competitive programming skills and **Stack Overflow** to engage with the global developer community by troubleshooting real-world bugs.  

This portfolio is not just a collection of accounts; it is a **living map of my technical journey**. By regularly updating these platforms, I aim to create a transparent record of my progress, ensuring that by my final year, I have a high-authority digital presence that attracts significant internship and placement opportunities in the AI field.

